  "rationale": "<p>Choice D is correct. The equation of a circle with center (h, k) and radius r is (x &minus; h)<sup>2</sup> + (y &minus; k)<sup>2</sup> = r<sup>2</sup>. With center (&minus;2, 3) and radius 7: (x &minus; (&minus;2))<sup>2</sup> + (y &minus; 3)<sup>2</sup> = 7<sup>2</sup>, i.e., (x + 2)<sup>2</sup> + (y &minus; 3)<sup>2</sup> = 49. Choices A and B have the wrong signs for the center coordinates. Choice C uses 7 instead of 49 for r<sup>2</sup>.</p>",
